<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,258,463]" pageId="2" pageNumber="215">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,214,258,283]" pageId="2" pageNumber="215">Note.</emphasis>
Although the 
<typeStatus box="[381,479,258,283]" pageId="2" pageNumber="215">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gertsch &amp; Davis" authorityYear="1940" box="[520,786,259,283]" class="Arachnida" family="Phrurolithidae" genus="Phonotimpus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="2" pageNumber="215" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="separatus">
<emphasis box="[520,786,259,283]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="215">Phonotimpus separatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has not been examined by us, the studied specimen was collected at the 
<typeStatus box="[327,375,295,319]" pageId="2" pageNumber="215">type</typeStatus>
locality and is consistent with most of the descriptive characters provided by 
<bibRefCitation pageId="2" pageNumber="215" refId="ref7001" refString="Gertsch, W. L. &amp; Davis, L. I. (1940) Report on a collection of spiders from Mexico III. American Museum Novitates, 1069, 1 - 22." type="journal article">Gertsch &amp; Davis (1940)</bibRefCitation>
, including the illustration of the epigynum. Dr. N. Platnick (American Museum of Natural History, 
<collectingRegion country="United States of America" name="New York" pageId="2" pageNumber="215">New York</collectingRegion>
) compared our figures of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gertsch &amp; Davis" authorityYear="1940" box="[499,635,367,390]" class="Arachnida" family="Phrurolithidae" genus="Phonotimpus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="2" pageNumber="215" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="separatus">
<emphasis box="[499,635,367,390]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="215">P. separatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with the 
<typeStatus box="[740,838,366,391]" pageId="2" pageNumber="215">holotype</typeStatus>
specimen and confirmed that they are conspecific.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
